title: BESydney welcomes the thought leadership of its AmbassadorsTravelandtourworld.com
text:
BESydney welcomes the thought leadership of its Ambassadors Published on : Wednesday, September 30, 2015
Business Events Sydney’s (BESydney) Ambassadors are leaders and visionaries that champion innovation and solutions for the future. A number of Ambassadors have recently been featured in the media. Read more about their stories:
Australian researchers, notably those at the Australian Research Council’s Centre of Excellence in Quantum Computation at the University of New South Wales, are considered to be perhaps two to three years ahead of overseas groups in creating the first, undisputed, truly useful quantum – a significant advantage in this competitive field.
Head of the Centre of Excellence, Professor Michelle Simmons, says that a working quantum computer will be a new era in computing for which there is no existing infrastructure, anywhere. But when a prototype 10 quantum bit (qbit) computer is up and running by 2018-20, as the centre intends, it will have worked out and patented the techniques for fabricating qbits to make the computers – detailed expertise that no one else will have.
